President Donald J. Trump issued a Presidential Memorandum on December 21, 2018, regarding the delegation of functions and authorities under Section 1245 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019. The memorandum delegates certain responsibilities to the Secretary of State and the Secretary of Defense. The Secretary of State is delegated functions and authorities in coordination with other departments and agencies through the National Security Presidential Memorandum-4 process, while the Secretary of Defense is delegated functions and authorities in coordination with other departments and agencies through the same process. The memorandum also states that these delegations apply to any future public law provisions that are the same or substantially the same as the provisions mentioned in the memorandum. The Secretary of State is instructed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.